WEBVTT

00:02.203 --> 00:04.803
[josh]
<i> barry is not happy at all.</i>

00:08.009 --> 00:09.641
I'm not going to let
the old man sweep that.

00:11.112 --> 00:13.712
I'm trying to fix this.

00:13.714 --> 00:17.950
If we can't get fish faster,
it's over.

00:18.019 --> 00:21.053
We're on the hook
for 3,000 pounds of fish
every week

00:21.122 --> 00:23.155
<i> For our clients</i>
<i> on the mainland.</i>

00:23.224 --> 00:25.524
So far, we've come up
like twice.

00:25.526 --> 00:27.526
<i> And last week,</i>
<i> we delivered late.</i>

00:28.496 --> 00:30.629
<i> Now barry wants a meeting.</i>

00:30.631 --> 00:31.964
Probably not good news.

00:33.634 --> 00:35.934
[barry] josh, I really
can't do this anymore.

00:36.036 --> 00:39.738
I'm running
this whole place over here,
and I'm depending on you guys

00:39.807 --> 00:43.008
And now you can't deliver
on time, man, that's...
That's important to me.

00:44.412 --> 00:46.211
[josh] all right.
Hey, barry, stop.

00:47.515 --> 00:49.748
I depended on you guys
for something.

00:49.817 --> 00:52.851
Restaurants are opening,
we're open.

00:52.920 --> 00:55.320
I'm doing 600 covers a night
and it's a [bleep] depending
on your quality

00:55.322 --> 00:57.523
And product coming
into my restaurant,
especially the time.

00:57.525 --> 00:59.124
If they're telling me
it's coming in on Friday,

00:59.126 --> 01:01.160
"oh, the plane didn't arrive."

01:01.228 --> 01:02.461
We [stammers] we're gonna do?

01:03.764 --> 01:04.963
I can't rely on you guys.

01:06.133 --> 01:07.533
Trying to get this
order completed.

01:07.634 --> 01:09.601
You know, we pushed
you guys over the top
to cover

01:09.603 --> 01:11.603
When nobody
else could deliver.

01:11.605 --> 01:12.805
We got this.

01:12.807 --> 01:14.406
We just need
a couple more days.

01:15.943 --> 01:17.309
Look, here's what's going
to happen.

01:17.311 --> 01:19.711
I'm going to let you finish
the current order,

01:19.713 --> 01:22.147
But I'm going to put
everything else on pause.

01:22.216 --> 01:24.349
Until you guys get
your [bleep] together.

01:24.451 --> 01:25.918
I just got to look elsewhere.

01:26.020 --> 01:28.420
-All right, man.
-All right, brother.

01:28.422 --> 01:29.521
Listen, I'm sorry, man.

01:29.523 --> 01:31.223
It's all good.
Sorry. I got you.

01:34.228 --> 01:36.028
Yeah!
Boom!

01:36.030 --> 01:37.996
I am captain, josh harris.

01:37.998 --> 01:39.398
I keep looking
at that picture

01:39.400 --> 01:40.999
<i> And he keeps looking back</i>
<i> at me.</i>

01:41.001 --> 01:45.604
<i> Phil harris was my father</i>
<i> and a legend</i>
<i> on the bering sea.</i>

01:45.606 --> 01:47.639
[phil] you can't get
any better than me.

01:47.708 --> 01:49.608
I'm just a smiling
[bleep] jack.

01:49.610 --> 01:51.810
[josh] <i> after a decade apart</i>

01:51.812 --> 01:54.813
<i> My older brother shane</i>
<i> is back by my side.</i>

01:54.815 --> 01:56.348
[shane] ...Fighting 'em still.

01:57.618 --> 02:00.052
[josh] <i> together, we're</i>
<i> fulfilling my dad's dream</i>

02:00.054 --> 02:01.920
<i> For an off-season</i>
<i> fishing business.</i>

02:01.922 --> 02:03.055
[shane grunts]

02:03.057 --> 02:04.756
[shane] that's for you phil.

02:04.758 --> 02:07.726
[josh] <i> but if we can't catc</i>
<i> what we need</i>
<i> in hawaiian waters...</i>

02:07.728 --> 02:10.896
If you're not gonna respect
our home then
don't come here.

02:10.898 --> 02:13.031
[josh] <i> we'll follow</i>
<i> the old man's footsteps.</i>

02:13.033 --> 02:14.433
[casey] we got tuna!

02:14.501 --> 02:16.902
Good. Client's alive.

02:16.904 --> 02:18.437
Wherever the trail leads...

02:19.807 --> 02:22.541
You put so much
into this here,

02:22.643 --> 02:24.109
And now you want to leave?

02:30.618 --> 02:32.351
[distant seagulls cawing]

02:38.425 --> 02:40.959
[josh] so what's this big plan
you got?

02:41.061 --> 02:43.395
[jeff] well, I want to show
you guys something.

02:43.397 --> 02:44.563
[josh] all right.

02:46.901 --> 02:48.500
All right, so check this out.

02:49.937 --> 02:54.606
So, we just came from kauai

02:54.608 --> 02:56.041
And we did that
because we know

02:56.043 --> 02:57.309
That the bite starts
usually in kauai,

02:57.311 --> 02:58.810
Because the fish arrive
here first.

02:58.812 --> 03:00.012
Oh, you know what,

03:00.014 --> 03:01.613
That didn't work out
very great.

03:01.615 --> 03:05.951
[jeff] yeah, but from here
they migrate south.

03:06.053 --> 03:08.253
They've migrated down to oahu,

03:08.322 --> 03:11.223
And the next stop
that they're going to hit
is this channel,

03:11.225 --> 03:12.524
Which is
the alenuihaha channel,

03:12.526 --> 03:14.426
-Above the kona coast.
-Okay.

03:14.428 --> 03:15.994
There's a big pinnacle
out here.

03:15.996 --> 03:17.629
They call it indianapolis.

03:17.631 --> 03:19.198
There's a really good chance
that the birds

03:19.200 --> 03:22.201
