we're there.

17:26.746 --> 17:30.114
[shane] <i> there's still</i>
<i> one card in my hand</i>
<i> that I haven't played.</i>

17:30.116 --> 17:32.450
But I knew there might be
a time when I need it.

17:34.287 --> 17:35.420
[josh] where are we headed?

17:36.623 --> 17:37.955
I got somebody down
at miloli'I.

17:38.024 --> 17:40.124
I want you to meet.

17:40.126 --> 17:42.093
Nelson kahele,

17:42.095 --> 17:44.028
He's a really good friend
of my dad,

17:44.030 --> 17:46.397
Friend of my family,
he's a friend to me.

17:46.399 --> 17:50.701
And he's fished out
of the south kona
his whole entire life.

17:53.206 --> 17:55.907
[shane] <i> milil's is located</i>
<i> in south kona.</i>

17:55.909 --> 17:58.943
<i> It's the last traditional</i>
<i> fishing village in hawaii.</i>

17:59.012 --> 18:00.411
They don't have power.

18:00.413 --> 18:02.413
They live
off of catchment water.

18:02.415 --> 18:03.648
They're self-sustaining.

18:05.752 --> 18:07.618
<i> And the fishermen,</i>

18:07.620 --> 18:10.221
