information easy.

18:10.223 --> 18:11.823
[josh]
<i> and this is where I'm from,</i>
<i> man.</i>

18:11.825 --> 18:14.058
Born and raised on here.

18:14.060 --> 18:15.827
Why haven't we come here
before?

18:18.731 --> 18:20.364
I have a hard time
coming down here.

18:22.402 --> 18:25.236
I was 16 when I left miloli'I.

18:25.305 --> 18:26.403
[josh] what happened?

18:28.708 --> 18:32.844
For my dad, fishing just
wasn't going to cut it.

18:32.912 --> 18:35.513
Um...[bleep]

18:36.816 --> 18:40.118
Broke his heart, broke mine.

18:40.120 --> 18:42.420
[shane]
<i> it wasn't just my father</i>
<i> leaving miloli'I.</i>

18:43.623 --> 18:48.326
<i> It was leaving his entire</i>
<i> lifestyle that he grew up in</i>

18:49.429 --> 18:50.661
<i> It was about survival.</i>

18:52.966 --> 18:56.534
But everybody down
in miloli'I was family.

18:57.804 --> 19:00.505
<i> And when we left,</i>
<i> it created some hard feeling</i>

19:02.642 --> 19:04.408
I hope this works.

19:04.410 --> 19:05.510
Yeah, me too.

19:06.746 --> 19:08.112
See this almost right here.

19:10.450 --> 19:12.150
[josh] it's brilliant today.

19:12.251 --> 19:15.820
[jeff] no, I think
if he's approached
the right way,

19:15.822 --> 19:17.155
Maybe he'll help us out.

19:22.829 --> 19:24.862
Hey.
How are you?

19:24.931 --> 19:26.129
[nelson] good, good, good.

19:26.131 --> 19:27.765
[jeff]
thank you for having us.
I appreciate it.

19:27.833 --> 19:29.233
Yeah...

19:29.335 --> 19:30.501
This is josh.
Josh, this is nelson.

19:30.503 --> 19:31.636
[josh] how are you doing,
my man?

19:31.737 --> 19:33.337
-Nice to meet you, brother.
-Nice to meet you too.

19:33.406 --> 19:38.943
This is one of the last true
ohana's from the big island.

19:39.045 --> 19:40.344
Yeah, yeah.

19:40.413 --> 19:41.512
[laughs]

19:43.216 --> 19:46.050
I was kind of explaining
to josh that, you know,

19:46.152 --> 19:48.819
Success on the water comes
with having a good network.

19:50.223 --> 19:53.324
I don't really
give information
out to anybody.

19:53.326 --> 19:57.428
If I feel that I don't like
to help you,

19:57.430 --> 19:59.430
I will tell you straight.

19:59.432 --> 20:00.665
[dog barking]

20:02.602 --> 20:04.802
Let me take you down,
take you guys down

20:04.804 --> 20:11.209
And show you
where everything started
in our, our family here.

20:11.211 --> 20:12.610
[josh] okay.

20:14.647 --> 20:16.814
[nelson]
<i> my, my grandfather, my dad,</i>

20:16.816 --> 20:18.816
My great grandfather, then,

20:18.818 --> 20:20.851
They all used
to fish off of this.

20:20.953 --> 20:22.186
-[josh] really?
-[nelson] yeah.

20:22.255 --> 20:26.290
This was how we used to go out
and catch opelu and even ahi.

20:26.292 --> 20:28.159
We seal this.

20:28.228 --> 20:29.527
[josh] it's crazy.

20:29.529 --> 20:31.629
A lot of memories, yeah?

20:31.631 --> 20:34.098
-No.
-A lot of memories, you know?

20:34.100 --> 20:38.035
This place made me the person
that I am today,
and so has he.

20:38.037 --> 20:39.804
And that was why I wanted
you to meet him.

20:40.907 --> 20:42.039
You know where y'all?

20:44.043 --> 20:46.410
You know this is your home.

20:46.412 --> 20:47.645
Thank you.

20:47.714 --> 20:49.814
You know, you cannot forget
your roots, you know.

20:51.351 --> 20:53.651
We got to get out there
and do what we've got
to do

20:53.720 --> 20:56.320
To support our family, yeah?

20:56.322 --> 20:57.455
Yeah, I mean,

20:57.556 --> 21:00.258
And I've made
a lot of sacrifices too.

21:00.359 --> 21:03.060
You know, and I looked
at a lot of the stuff
my dad did.

21:04.130 --> 21:06.330
It didn't make
any sense until now.

21:06.332 --> 21:08.633
You know, you got
to provide for your family.

21:08.734 --> 21:11.602
